<h3 class="date"><a href="/2012/jan/23/">&#x27a0;</a> January 23, 2012</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="salary-negotiation-make-more-m" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.kalzumeus.com/2012/01/23/salary-negotiation/">Salary Negotiation: Make More Money, Be More Valued</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>&#8220;The first rule is what everyone tells you it is: Never give a number first&#8221; and other important info for engineers.</p>

<p>(Fun fact: The only time in my career I&#8217;ve ever offered an answer to the question &#8220;What sort of salary are you expecting?&#8221;, I gave myself a 33% bump over my then-current salary-and-bonus, and it was immediately accepted by the recruiter. I still wonder what I could have made.)</p>

